How should illusions able can kill be handled? I say like any other death
magic, with the special effect that they work by illusions.

Allowing your average illusion spell to be able to induce death makes it
damn powerful, probably toppling game balance.

The main point behind illusions seems to be that you believe in them, and make
them actually happen. However, someone affected by a disease would rarely give
in to it, there is hope as long as there is breath. The body's inner workings
won't be too much affected by conscient thought anyway. You might rule that
this struggle of the body against the imaginated disease is the actual cause
of death, antigenes, shock, etc, but it assumes that our medicinical knowledge
and magic can exist together, and further, that one can induce the effects of
illusionary germs by playing with perception. IMO, this is too farfetched to
be used in games. Death magic is much easier.
   Benedikt
