Well, I do allow illusions to kill, but it is very difficult. The first
time an illusion does something that would cause damage (were it real),
the victim is allowed another save. If it fails, the victim believes
he/she has been injured, and the damage is recorded seperately from 'real'
damage that the victim has taken. Any additonal attacks by the illusion
against the victim grant no free saves. If the victim should ever fall
unconscious from damage sustained, no problem; they are out. If the
real and illusionary damage totaled kills the character (less than
-10 in AD&D, or if a death roll is forced and failed in GURPS), roll
vs HT+5 in GURPS or make a system shock roll in AD&D. If the roll fails,
the person suffers major heart attack or stroke, and dies.

