On the topic of this illusion business, what would be the true limitations
of other spells?

Could a magic-user shape change into a virus that he knew is a cause of
a plague and kill an entire town if not country-side?

Normal illusions should not be able to kill.  There are the more powerful
spells that do that.  A normal illusion could fool someone into thinking
that they have been killed and the shock could send them into
unconsciousness (Dm's option) but on the question if they die, they may
be given a system shock roll to avoid the heart attack idea of the scare
of dying.  But I would say that at that instant (if they make their first
system shock roll to avoid unconsciousness) that the illusion is broken.
The reason behind this is the idea "I should have been killed.  What
happened?".  At that moment that doubt enters the persons mind the
illusion is broken...  They are sitting thier with pieces of them
hanging all over (all illisionary) and they are fine.  They could have
an arm blown off and if they fall to the ground and throw their arms out
to catch themselves (a reflex to throw out both) then both will catch
them and they will feel an invisible force holding them up where their
arm used to be.  Again, the idea of that instant of doubt...  To do
anything otherwise makes low level illusion spells more powerful than
a power word kill that is an 8th level spell (I think)...  this is most
non-triumphant (for the villians that is, hahahahahahaha)....

